    m_Alignment: 0
    m_AlignByGeometry: 0
    m_RichText: 1
    m_HorizontalOverflow: 0
    m_VerticalOverflow: 1
    m_LineSpacing: 1
  m_Text: 'FORMULA

    h = 1/2 gt^2

    g = 2h/t^2


    METHOD

    Use different
    measured heights. Release the ball from rest and allow the automatic landing
    detector to stop the timer.


    GRAPH

    Plot t^2 on X and 2h on Y. The slope
    is g.


    GOOD PRACTICE

    - Do not push the ball.

    - Keep the landing
    plate fixed.

    - Record at least three heights.

    - Use metres and seconds.'
